[
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm probably holding it wrong, but after adding a new sync function returning a future, i.e.:</p>\n<p><code>execute: func(query: string, params: list&lt;value&gt;) -&gt; future&lt;result&lt;u64, tx-error&gt;&gt;;</code></p>\n<p>, implementing it on the host-side using a FutureReader and rebuilding the rust guest component, I'm seeing:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">Failed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">instantiate</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WIT</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">component</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"../../client/testfixture/wasm/wasm_guest_testfixture.wasm\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">component</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">imports</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">tr</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ailbase</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"nc\">database</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">sqlite</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"mf\">0.1.2</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">but</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">matching</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">implementation</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">was</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">linker</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">This</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">may</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">happen</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">server</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">and</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">component</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">are</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ABI</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">incompatible</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compatible</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">versions</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">update</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rebuild</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">component</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">server</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">binary</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">update</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">your</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">server</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span>\n<span class=\"n\">o</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">more</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">up</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">date</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">components</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">First</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">party</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">components</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">can</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">be</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">updated</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">easily</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">running</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"cp\">$</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">trail</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">components</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">update</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">downloaded</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">https</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"c1\">//github.com/trailbaseio/trailbase/releases.</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">thread</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">main</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1672464</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">panicked</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">crates</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">wasm</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">runtime</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">axum</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">examples</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">standalone</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">52</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n<span class=\"nc\">called</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">on</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">an</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Wasmtime</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">component</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">imports</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">trailbase</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"nc\">database</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">sqlite</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"mf\">0.1.2</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">but</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">matching</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">implementation</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">was</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">linker</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">Caused</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">by</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">export</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">execute</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">has</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wrong</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">type</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mismatch</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">async</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I suspect there's a disconnect between the host-side and guest-side \"bindgen\"...maybe <span aria-label=\"woman shrugging\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f937-200d-2640\" role=\"img\" title=\"woman shrugging\">:woman_shrugging:</span>. Happy to provide more context <span aria-label=\"pray\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f64f\" role=\"img\" title=\"pray\">:pray:</span></p>",
        "id": 607868397,
        "sender_full_name": "Ignatz",
        "timestamp": 1783004451
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How are you adding the host function to the linker?  Are you using <code>wasmtime-wit-bindgen</code> or calling <code>Linker::func_wrap_async</code> or <code>Linker::func_wrap_concurrent</code> directly?</p>",
        "id": 607888286,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Dice",
        "timestamp": 1783009661
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Simply calling the bindgen generated add_to_linker function: <a href=\"https://github.com/trailbaseio/trailbase/blob/wasip3/crates/wasm-runtime-host/src/lib.rs#L136\">https://github.com/trailbaseio/trailbase/blob/wasip3/crates/wasm-runtime-host/src/lib.rs#L136</a> <span aria-label=\"pray\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f64f\" role=\"img\" title=\"pray\">:pray:</span></p>",
        "id": 607897555,
        "sender_full_name": "Ignatz",
        "timestamp": 1783012556
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, it does seem like there's a mismatch between the host- and guest-side generated bindings in that one side thinks <code>execute</code> is an async function and the other side thinks it's a non-async function, which could happen if two, contradictory WIT definitions are used.  Are you using recent versions of both Wasmtime and <code>wit-bindgen</code> and can you confirm that the same WIT file is being used on both sides?</p>",
        "id": 607908831,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Dice",
        "timestamp": 1783015606
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ack to everything. I'm using the latest versions of wasmtime and bindgen. The guest codegen is here: <a href=\"https://github.com/trailbaseio/trailbase/blob/wasip3/crates/wasm-runtime-guest/src/lib.rs#L6\">https://github.com/trailbaseio/trailbase/blob/wasip3/crates/wasm-runtime-guest/src/lib.rs#L6</a> and the host codegen is here: <a href=\"https://github.com/trailbaseio/trailbase/blob/wasip3/crates/wasm-runtime-host/src/host.rs#L50\">https://github.com/trailbaseio/trailbase/blob/wasip3/crates/wasm-runtime-host/src/host.rs#L50</a> (maybe me specifying the import flags is the issue?). Anyway, the WIT is the same and the function was just added (<a href=\"https://github.com/trailbaseio/trailbase/blob/wasip3/crates/wasm-runtime-guest/wit/trailbase/database/world.wit#L22\">https://github.com/trailbaseio/trailbase/blob/wasip3/crates/wasm-runtime-guest/wit/trailbase/database/world.wit#L22</a>), so if they'd use stale definitions i'd rather expect that one side is missing the stub <span aria-label=\"shrug\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f937\" role=\"img\" title=\"shrug\">:shrug:</span></p>",
        "id": 607914559,
        "sender_full_name": "Ignatz",
        "timestamp": 1783017680
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ok, I don't know offhand what's going wrong.  Would you be able to provide a list of steps to repro the error message?  If so, I can take a closer look.</p>",
        "id": 607915539,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Dice",
        "timestamp": 1783018050
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's very kind.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">clone</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">https</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"c1\">//github.com/trailbaseio/trailbase.git</span>\n<span class=\"n\">cd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">trailbase</span>\n<span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">checkout</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wasip3</span>\n<span class=\"n\">cd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">crates</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">wasm</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">runtime</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">axum</span>\n<span class=\"n\">cargo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"n\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">standalone</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"o\">=../../</span><span class=\"n\">client</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">testfixture</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">wasm</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 607916258,
        "sender_full_name": "Ignatz",
        "timestamp": 1783018327
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This loads prebuilt component checked in at <code>&lt;repo&gt;/client/testfixture/wasm/wasm_guest_testfixture.wasm</code>. The component lives here: <code>&lt;repo&gt;/client/testfixture/guests/rust</code> and can be rebuilt with:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">cd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">repo</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;/</span><span class=\"n\">client</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">testfixture</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">guests</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 607919809,
        "sender_full_name": "Ignatz",
        "timestamp": 1783019609
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks.  Looks like this is a bug in Wasmtime 46 and earlier, fixed in <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/commit/72403200a425788850a97c6d9730dc583135e673\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/commit/72403200a425788850a97c6d9730dc583135e673</a>.  If you try updating to Wasmtime's <code>main</code> branch, it should be fixed there.</p>",
        "id": 607920070,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Dice",
        "timestamp": 1783019717
    }
]